					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252598" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;" >TyGently</a></span> <span class="odate time_1429295557 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Apr 2015 18:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2272477">
									

<p>I have to say, I'm not really loving the focus on Adams so far. There's been focus on her, on what she does, what other characters think of her&#8230; to me, she seems like a wisecracking, cynical LGBT character with no discernible personality traits. It's just not an interesting story to see, in my opinion, of course.</p>
<p>There are plenty of characters I do like and have been excited to see more of, but Adams just isn't one of them for me. So far, we've seen Adams squabble with Clef, spend three tales with Iris (which I especially disliked because it seemed almost as if the tales were spiting the reader for asking them to have purpose near the end) and now, try on a super-suit, which does super things.</p>
<p>I respect you very much as a writer, but I just felt I should share my opinion on Adams as a central character.</p>

							</div>

								
					
