					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-reach" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1779895); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1779895&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252598" alt="Dr Reach" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1779895)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-reach" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1779895); return false;" >Dr Reach</a></span> <span class="odate time_1429355204 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Apr 2015 11:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2272837">
									

<blockquote>
<p>(&#8230;) but the technology here is also from mothballed projects.)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>See, this is the reason why I <em>can</em> accept this. But this is also the reason I don't get why the Foundation would go from &quot;Let's Weaponize Humanoid Anomalies&quot; to &quot;WE'VE MADE ALL THIS NON-SENTIENT ANOMALOUS TECH BUT THE OTHER THING WENT SOUTH, SO SOUTH MAN, ALL THE WAY TO KINGEATER'S CASTLE SO LONG STORY SHORT WE'RE NOT USING ANY ANOMALOUS TECH NOW&quot;. There seems to be little to no transition between those two points. I mean, this is clearly <em>working</em> tech, likely a very successful prototype of which we've seen no flaws yet&#8230; but it's simply too good for me to accept that the Foundation would have it just laying around.</p>
<p>Furthermore, SCP-2000 seems to be an inherited piece of tech that survived from previous paradigm shifts. I would imagine it's a the fractured product of a number of past iterations where the current rules and concerns do not apply. The Archivist probably knows what's up on that regard, but it's not a stretch of imagination that 2000 and 2000-like tech would not be made, or even attempted, by the Foundation between Omega-7 and Alpha-9.</p>
<p>But we're still lacking details and aspects of the thing. So, you know.</p>
<p><sub>This is all headcanon, as usual, so it's not really relevant.</sub></p>

